metadata.name: Dolphin Rainbow Dance
metadata.description:
Superior to human sight
Your sound waves and reverberates
To be in tune in natures light
To be in touch and resonate

excerpt from Spirit Dolphin
By The Terry Tree

The sea around the Black Isle near to Inverness in Scotland is nowadays world famous for it’s dolphin spotting! There are around 200 Bottlenose dolphins that live all year in the chilly waters of the Moray Firth and around the East Coast of Scotland and half this population are seen regularly along the Black Isle coastline, which is the distant land in artwork.  Photo taken from Inverness side.

Collection: Scottish Landscapes
Artist: EAMZY
Year: 2022. 
Edition: NFT 1/1.
